Day 11. Newport News, VA Nov 19

A lovely theatre on a University Campus. 

I spent the morning walking round their lovely wilderness and then saw the fancy campus that looked very Disney World. 

There was a kid in the show who looked like a mini me. @pauldabek got his new show title then snuggled with @hyunjoonkim_artist on the bus. 
#magic #magicshow #illusionists #mentalist #tour #backstage #theatre

location.city_name: Belk Theater at Blumenthal Performing Arts Center

social_posts.post_text:
Day 12. Charlotte, NC.  Nov 20

A beautiful room here for a sold out show. I remember this crowd being amazing. 

I took my usual walk around and found some art. 

After the show I went to Hooters with the team and got them to change the sports to cartoons. 

#magic #magicshow #illusionists #mentalist #tour #backstage #theatre

Day 13. Hershey PA  Nov 21

A historic old theatre, which meant we were tightly packed backstage but had a fun show and a lovely crowd. 

I went to Hershey Park. The rides were closed but the chocolate World was open and I got a free chocolate. Yum yum. 

My Bath had three taps. So there’s that. 

#magic #magicshow #illusionists #mentalist #tour #backstage #theatre

Day 15. Hartford, Connecticut.  Nov 22

A cold day but excellent catering with an actual chef on site cooking. He did set off the fire alarm though. 

Not much going on in this city, there was a ballet on in the theatre next door. Not a huge amount of memories here so feels like it was getting to the Groundhog Day part of the tour. 

#magic #magicshow #illusionists #mentalist #tour #backstage #theatre
Fun few days working on the magic for the U.K. tour of @charliechoc_uk  What a wonderful bunch of people that cast and crew are. Thanks to @theatreillusion for trusting me with his magic!

Day 16.  Red Bank NJ.  Nov 23

A tiny venue that barely fit the show but a lovely audience. Also excellent catering with pie and NY Bagels. 

A charming little town on the banks of the river. Lovely one to walk around. Supposedly Jon Bon Jovi and Jon Stewart live here. Or maybe it was Bruce Springsteen? I forget. Anyway. I’d like to go back. 

#magic #magicshow #illusionists #mentalist #tour #backstage #theatre

Day 17 & 18, Cincinnati, Ohio.  Nov 24 & 25

A long overnight drive meant we got into Cincinnati mid morning on Thanksgiving. So I watched the parade on the bus with James. 

Had a thanksgiving dinner with @shannonko11 @jamesmoremagic and @pauldabek but we didn’t go on the ice bumpercars. I didn’t get a photo of us all. Maybe Shazza did?

The next day we did the show but we had to bring audiences through the pass door to get them on stage. Quick load out as the next day was a double show day in the Fabulous Fox St Louis. 

#magic #magicshow #illusionists #mentalist #tour #backstage #theatre

Day 19, St Louis Missouri.  Nov 26

The most amazing venue with two shows here. I was lucky enough to play it a few years ago and it’s a joy to be back. 

The shows were 90mins with no interval which means for a very stressful show for me but both were a real delight. 

Backstage this theatre is just full of memories of shows I love. What a history. What a room. What a life!

#magic #magicshow #illusionists #mentalist #tour #backstage #theatre

Day 20. Louisville, Kentucky. Nov 27

I remember waking up on the bus to find we were parked on a side street near the theatre. I then got lost trying to find the theatre. 

It was a small but lovely little room, not much space backstage but a fun show. 

I took my first Lime scooter out for a look around town but it was a Sunday and nearly everywhere was closed. 

Post show was a long drive to Joliet, IL and a day off. 

#theillusionists #magicshow #backstage #tour #mentalist

Went on a @virginvoyages and had the best time. Adults only, amazing food, stylish ship, no gratuity, all the bad stuff about cruising - they’ve got rid of it. Can’t recommend it enough #travel #cruise #virginvoyages

I use stories a lot but forget about the grid. So here’s a few more photos from our time on @virginvoyages. Tbh is mainly photos of the food. Plus what I sang in the karaoke booth. #cruise #travel #virginvoyages #food #foodie #cruisefood #ahoysailor #cruiseline

A quick 24 hours in New York. If time is of the essence than flying Blade into the city is the way to go. Plus you feel like Logan Roy. Then bagels for lunch and @nynybway for theatrical delights. #newyork #nyc #bagel #blade #flyblade #helicopter
Lots of fun to work with the amazing @theatreillusion on @charliechoc_uk tour and catch up with the team in Cardiff this week. #theatre #magic #illusion #consulting

Cooking With Cox: The perfect six hour red sauce for pasta recipe. Super simple, amazingly tasty. Enjoy! #recipe #Italian #pasta #tomato #tomatosauce #pasta #pastasauce #cooking #food #tasty #cookingwithcox #whatsfordinner
Having a wonderful time reading some minds on the glorious @seabourncruise Ovation. A ship full of lovely, friendly people. It’s been a joy to get into their heads.

So excited to see @mariothemagician getting ready for his @edfringe shows @underbellyedinburgh. Get your tickets now! I saw his show earlier this year and had to make sure more people saw it, so I helped bring it to the festival. It is the greatest family magic show ever. Kids will adore it, you’ll love it. Full of heart, comedy, robots and magic. Spread the word!

Had such an amazing time @magicliveconvention. So wonderful to see old friends and make new ones. I hope everyone who came to my lecture / focus sessions took something away from it. And I hope you all enjoyed my act in the show. Yay Vegas!
What a dream of a theatre to play! #disneydream #disneycruise #magic #mindreader
A super fun week getting to play with the minds of the wonderful humans aboard @seabourncruise

Back on tour. Catch me in and around the US and Canada this holiday season. Full dates at my website, link in the profile. Obvs. See you there for some festive Cox. @theillusionistslive #magic #theillusionists #tour #mindreader
Tour Dates! See you there? @theillusionistslive #theillusionists #mindreader #theatre #magic
Delighted to be back creating magic for @laplanduk this year. It’s even more magical than ever before. #laplanduk #magic #creative #illusions #christmas

MEET THE MENTALIST: Chris Cox @magiccox  knows what you’re thinking. You’re thinking, who the hell is Chris Cox? He’s a multi-award winning ‘mind reader who can’t read minds’ and the only one in history to have played New York’s Broadway, London’s West End & Sydney Opera House - seen live by over 750,000 people worldwide. He’s the star of the BBC’s Chris Cox’s Mind Boggling Magic & Killer Magic and has been featured on NBC’s The Today Show. Outside of performing Chris is on the creative team for Harry Potter & The Cursed Child, Lapland UK, DC Comic’s Park Row Restaurant and Punchdrunk. The UK’s Guardian Newspaper says he is “one of the most exciting entertainers in Britain,” and The New York Times says he’s ‘a hyperactive Harry Potter who knows what you’re thinking.’ Tickets for The Illusionists 🪄 Magic of the Holidays 🪄 are on sale now. 

#MeetTheCast #theilusionists #magicoftheholidays #magic #magician #holidaymagic #chriscox #thementalist

Tour Day 1. Sioux City, Iowa. 
Lovely autumnal days greeted us in Sioux City where we teche’ed and opened the show. Our amazing team got everything ready in 4 days.

Always feels a bit weird doing festive stuff early November but the audience quickly got into the Christmas spirit. 

#theillusonists #magicoftheholidays #magicshow #magic #backstage #theatre #mentalist

Tour Day 2. Cedar Rapids, lowa.

A sleepless night with toothache lead to a long 4 hour bus trip to the Paramount theatre and then ann emergency dentist. Now on antibiotics and painkillers hoping that they can put off needing a root canal. 

I did the show very tired and in pain; hoping stage Chris would show up when I got in front of an audience. Luckily he did and we had a really fun show which at least for a short time helped me forget the pain. 

#theillusonists #magicoftheholidays #magicshow #magic #backstage #theatre #mentalist

Tour Day 3.  Omaha, Nebraska. 

I remember playing this theatre a few days before the tour was called off due to Covid in 2020. That show had an air of impending  doom so it was lovely to play it with an air of holiday joy. 

A truly manic audience and me on painkillers made for a fun show. Crazy nonsense such as the curtain falling on-top of my props and two local crew just bringing another prop on to the middle of the stage midway through my act made it all the more crazy. 

#theillusonists #magicoftheholidays #magicshow #magic #backstage #theatre #mentalist

Tour Day 4. Day Off. New York

A day off meant a whistle stop 24 hours in New York. 

I got to spend time at the home of @mariothemagician and his amazing family. I saw his show at a magic convention earlier this year and fell in love with it. I produced it with them at the Edinburgh Fringe this year and am now co-producing their run @sohoplayhousenyc 

It is the greatest family magic show ever. Full of amazing magic, love, heart, joy, chaos and ROBOTS! It was so amazing to see all ages have the best time. I genuinely think every kid who sees the show will grow up to be a better human. And every adult will leave it trying to make the world a better place. He runs till the end of December and you simply must try see it. 

I also go to hang out with Emily Jillette who isn’t on insta and @len.testa who is but we forgot to get a photo. 

Next stop. Chicago. 

#theillusonists #magicoftheholidays #magicshow #magic #backstage #theatre #mentalist

Tour Day 5. Day Off. Chicago

After a manic day in NYC it was lovely to have a slightly more relaxed day in Chicago. Albeit one with tooth pain still. But I did get to run through Chicago airport with the Home Alone music playing g 

I had a nice morning walking round and visiting Trader Joes. Then a fun night as the guests of the wonderful @lucydarling at the Chicago institution which is @zinzanni

What a fun show it is! They built a spiegeltent on the 14th floor of a building and create a wonderful dinner show complete with a dance for each course. A wonderful mix of circus, variety and magic followed with splendid company. 

#theillusonists #magicoftheholidays #magicshow #magic #backstage #theatre #mentalist

Tour Day 6 to something. I’ve lost track. Chicago

What a super cool city Chicago is and what wild audiences we have already had for our first few shows in Chicago. 

The Cadillac Palace theatre is beautiful and historic and the crowds have been loving it. 

I enjoyed a 9am emergency dentist appointment before a two show day, so have been in pain all week but hoping I turn a corner the next few days. The nice thing is when doing the show I don’t feel the pain as I’m busy reading minds. 

I write this as it’s Thanksgiving morning. I’m watching the parade on TV hoping to see the Bluey balloon. Priorities. 

#theillusonists #magicoftheholidays #magicshow #magic #backstage #theatre #mentalist #chicago @broadwayinchicago @theillusionistslive

Tour. Chicago, Cadillac Palace Theatre. 

A mighty fine week in Chicago including a bonus day off for Thanksgiving. 

We were met with full houses of audience members who gave us wonderful responses. I particular enjoyed getting some big roars of approval at the end of my control routine. 

#theillusonists #magicoftheholidays #magicshow #magic #backstage #theatre #mentalist

Tour. Toronto. Princess Of Wales Theatre 

Big fan of Toronto. A great city full of wonderful food and secret underground walkways to stay warm. 

The shows have been so much fun here, always full with audiences who are really into it. It’s been a treat. 

#theillusonists #magicoftheholidays #magicshow #magic #backstage #theatre #mentalist

Tour. Toronto / Niagara Falls 

A final few shows in Toronto where we continued to eat great food before hopping on to the tour bus and heading to our next stop. 

But first we had a 5am break at Niagara Falls, and boy was it worth waking up for. 

#theillusonists #magicoftheholidays #magicshow #magic #backstage #theatre #mentalist #niagarafalls

Tour. Williamsport PA, New Brunswick NJ, Newark NJ 

A few hops down the east coast for some magical fun. Extra delighted as I got to see friends @mariothemagician @len.testa in Newark

#theillusonists #magicoftheholidays #magicshow #magic #backstage #theatre #mentalist

Tour. Boston MA. Emerson Colonial Theatre

Three days and four shows in Boston in this beautiful and historic theatre. La Cage Aux Follies and Moulin Rouge premiered there. Neil Simon did most of his work there. And now I’ve read minds there. 

Penn & Teller were in town doing their show down the road so I got to spend the afternoon catching up with Penn which is always a delight. 

#theillusonists #magicoftheholidays #magicshow #magic #backstage #theatre #mentalist

Tour. Williams Center at Cape Fear, Wilmington NC. Galliard Auditorium, Charleston, SC. Walt Disney Theatre at the Dr Philips Centre, Orlando, FL

A week on the tour bus visiting these lovely places. Full houses full of delighted audiences full of holiday cheer. 

Wilmington was a beautiful old town with a fantastic river walk, Charleston steeped in history like a small NOLA and Orlando was, well. Orlando. I managed to see friends and get in a quick visit to Disney Springs. I also got to play my third Walt Disney Theatre. 

#theillusonists #magicoftheholidays #magicshow #magic #backstage #theatre #mentalist

Tour.  Van Wezel, Sarasota FL. Mahaffey, St Petersburg FL. Islands Of Adventure then home to London. 

The last two days for me on the tour. The purple palace (perhaps owned by Barney or Grimace) gave us a wild show in Sarasota followed by a fun finish by the sea in St Pete’s. 

Then my travel day started with a few hours at Islands Of Adventure before a jaunt across the Atlantic. 

What a wonderful cast and crew I got to work with on this tour. It was so much fun with brilliant audiences across North America. I never take for granted how lucky I am to get to entertain people all over the world. I think we played to around 50k people on this tour. How amazing!

#theillusonists #magicoftheholidays #magicshow #magic #backstage #theatre #mentalist
Always a total pleasure to blow minds for a living.
I’ve played Broadway, London’s West End, Sydney Opera House and now (checks notes) Lincoln, CA at Thunder Valley Casino Resort. Feb 2. Quite the line up for this one. It’s going to be a good show.
